Sir Stirling Moss won 212 races in his 14-year career before a crash at Goodwood in 1962 ended his career . 
  The 85-year-old has reunited with the refurbished Austin-Healey Sprite he drove in 1962 . 
  Sir Stirling said he sees fitness as a 'way of life' and does 77 press-ups a day . 
  He also revealed he has half a bottle of Chardonnay a day  . 
  He has also swapped electric car for a Renault Twizy that has a top speed of 50mph . 
 